# Coding Standards

- Keep responses concise and actionable.
- Never make automatic code changes; provide suggestions only.
- Show code snippets in every technical answer.
- Prefer clear naming, small methods, and minimal side effects.
- For C# and WPF examples, use explicit, readable patterns.
- Always use CamelCase.
- Prefer C# concise features, such as automatic getter/setter and event callback.

## Example Suggestion Style

